title: Stalk With The Earthmother
objective: Sneak into the Venture Company mine southeast of Thunder Bluff and collect 5 Seaforium Mining Charges from carts of blasting supplies, then return them to Boarton Shadetotem in Thunder Bluff.
description: I sense in you a hidden talent for the subtle arts, shaman.  Use this mask to infilrate the nearby Venture Company mine and steal their supplies.  It may not seem like a convincing disguise, but a skilled rogue can slip past any guard with naught but a winning smile and a cunning distraction.  I believe this capability lies within you as well.
_progress: We'll need to work on your stealth skills, <class>.  I heard you approaching as soon as you set foot on the mesa.
_complete: Hmm... perhaps disguises are not your strength.
name: Stalk With The Earthmother

title: Stalk With The Earthmother
objective: Gather 8 Windfury Cones north of Thunder Bluff, use them with the Mortar and Pestle, then return to Boarton Shadetotem in Thunder Bluff with the result.
description:
I speak to you from your future, when the Horde faces threats you cannot imagine.  Since the others cannot see me, I rely on you to learn my skills and pass them to the tribe.

Maybe your skills lie with poisons, not disguises.  The Harpies to the north nest in a tree which produces a resin of potent toxicity.  Gather the fallen cones around the nests, then crush them into a salve.  When applied to a blade this salve will sear your opponent's wounds into their flesh and turn their blood to salt.
_progress: Be careful with the salve once you are finished, <class>.  Even skin contact could be quite painful.
_complete:
<class>, this is not the venomous salve I asked for.  What you have brought me is pine nut butter.  Are you sure you followed my instructions?

This will be of far more use spread on some spice bread than on a dagger.  Although you would be quite formidable against a foe with a nut allergy.
name: Stalk With The Earthmother

title: A Hunter's Strength
objective: Defeat Githyiss the Vile in Shadowthread Cave and recover the lost rune. Learn the rune, then report back to Ayanna Everstride in Shadowglen.
description:
A hunter draws strength from their connection and respect for all creatures, not just their pets. You will hunt and slay many beasts in service to the Alliance, but even in battle you must respect your foe.

My previous apprentice used a mystical rune to augment her skills, but foolishly attempted to practice on the largest of the spiders in the cave to the north, a creature we have named Githyiss the Vile. Her disrespect led to her demise.

Slay Githyiss - but do not underestimate its strength.
_progress: When you have slain Githyiss, recover the rune and learn its magic.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

There are many such runes throughout Azeroth. Seek them out, as they will help along your journey.
name: A Hunter's Strength

title: Relics of the Kaldorei
objective: Recover the relic from the grellkin in Shadowglen. Follow the relic's guidance to learn a new ability, then report back to Mardant Strongoak.
description:
The kaldorei are an ancient people, and our lost relics can be found across Azeroth. Through these relics, the spirits can teach you ways to strengthen your connection to the Dream.

The grellkin have stolen one such relic. Slay them and retrieve the relic, then follow its guidance to learn a new combat technique. Return to me when you have done this.
_progress: What has the relic taught you?
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune you have learned to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

Seek out more of our lost relics along your travels.
name: Relics of the Kaldorei

title: Second-Story Work
objective: Retrieve the rune from the hidden idol, then use it to learn a new ability. Afterwards, return to Frahun Shadewhisper.
description:
I have prepared a training exercise for you, <name>. There is an idol of an owl on the roof of this building. You should be able to see it from the south entrance. Inside the idol is a hidden compartment containing an engraved rune.

Make your way to the roof, find and memorize the rune hidden in the idol, and return to me.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

There are many such runes throughout Azeroth. Seek them out, as they will help along your journey.
name: Second-Story Work

title: Meditation on Elune
objective: Kneel at the moonwell to meditate on Elune, then use the memory to learn a new ability. Afterwards, return to Shanda in Shadowglen.
description:
Joining the Alliance has strengthened our people, but we must not forget that we are Kaldorei. Our connection to Elune is at the core of our being.

Clear your mind, <name>, and focus on my voice. I will share with you an ancient memory of our kind. Go to the moonwell to the north and kneel in the sacred waters to meditate on Elune's mysteries. Once you have focused your thoughts, you will be able to make sense of this memory and learn a new technique. Return to me when you have done this.
_complete:
Elune will likely grant you more memories along your travels. You can meditate at the moonwells across Azeroth to clear your thoughts and interpret these memories.

Understanding more complex visions may require the help of our fellow priests from the Alliance. Do not be afraid to learn from their faith, <name>. Tyrande teaches that the Holy Light worshipped by the humans and the Light of Elune are closely related.
name: Meditation on Elune

title: Amidst the Shadowed Webs
objective: Slay webwood spiders in Shadowthread Cave and recover the lost rune. Learn the rune, then report back to Alyissia in Shadowglen.
description:
The warriors of the Alliance have much to teach you, but you must also seek out new techniques on your own.

There is a cave to the north infested by webwood spiders. Another fledgling warrior ventured into the cave some time ago, and never returned. He was experimenting with engraving mystical runes onto his equipment to improve his combat prowess.

Find the rune among the spiders and learn this technique yourself.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

There are many such runes throughout Azeroth. Seek them out, as they will help along your journey.
name: Amidst the Shadowed Webs

title: A Trial of Fitness
objective: Find the Hidden Cache in the cliffs behind Frang. Learn the rune inside, then report back to Frang in the Valley of Trials.
description:
Above all else, a warrior of the Horde must be of strong body. On your journey, you will undergo many trials of stamina and endurance. 

To this end, I have hidden a cache among the cliffs behind me. You can see it if you stand by the fire in the center of the village. Reaching it will be no easy feat. Within the cache is a rune of great power.

Your test is to find this rune, and return when you have learned its secrets.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

There are many such runes throughout Azeroth. Seek them out, as they will help along your journey.
name: A Trial of Fitness

title: Atop the Cliffs
objective: Find the Hidden Cache in the cliffs surrounding the Valley of Trials. Learn the rune inside, then report back to Rwag in The Den.
description:
I have prepared a training exercise for you, <name>. I have hidden a cache among the cliffs nearby. You can see it if you stand by the fire in the center of the village. Within the cache is a rune of great power.

Your test is to acquire this rune, and return when you have learned its secrets.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

There are many such runes throughout Azeroth. Seek them out, as they will help along your journey.
name: Atop the Cliffs

title: Hunt for the Rune
objective: Find the lost rune by slaying scorpids in the Valley of Trials. Learn the rune's power, then report back to Jen'sahn.
description:
A hunter draws strength from their connection to the natural world. On your journey, you will track quarry through all manner of harsh terrain, surviving only by your wits.

Not long ago, another fledgling hunter sadly failed in this. He went out to hunt scorpids, and never returned. He was experimenting with engraving mystical runes onto his equipment to improve his combat prowess.

Find his rune among the scorpids nearby, and return when you have learned its secrets.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

There are many such runes throughout Azeroth. Seek them out, as they will help along your journey.
name: Hunt for the Rune

title: Icons of Power
objective: Find the stolen icon by slaying scorpids in the Valley of Trials. Learn its power, then report back to Shikrik.
description:
Shamanism is an ancient practice, <name>. Many artifacts, full of spiritual energy, can be found across Azeroth. I had recently discovered an icon of notable power myself, but it was stolen by those pesky scorpids.

One of them is likely carrying it around, thinking it a shiny curio to be used as a decoration for their nest. 

When you find the icon, learn its power and return to me.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

There are many such runes throughout Azeroth. Seek them out, as they will help along your journey.
name: Icons of Power

title: Stolen Power
objective: Find the stolen rune inside of the Burning Blade Coven. Learn its power, then report back to Nartok in The Den.
description:
I've been experimenting with a new type of magic - a rune which can channel fel energies to fuel powerful spells. I would share this power with you, but it was stolen by one of those pesky Burning Blade familiars.

Go to their coven, to the north, and see if you can find my rune stashed among their possessions. In my experience, the familiars tend to hide their plunder in hard to find places. 

Once you find the rune, learn its magic and report back to me. I would like to see my experiment put to us
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

There are many such runes throughout Azeroth. Seek them out, as they will help along your journey.
name: Stolen Power

title: The Lost Rune
objective: Find the lost rune within Echo Ridge Mine and use it to learn a new ability, then report back to Llane Beshere in Northshire.
description:
The warriors of the Alliance have much to teach you, but you must also seek out new techniques on your own.

Another young warrior recently ventured into the Echo Ridge Mine. She was experimenting with engraving mystical runes onto her equipment to improve her combat prowess.

I suspect she was overwhelmed when the kobolds captured the mine. Find the rune among the kobolds and learn this technique yourself.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

There are many such runes throughout Azeroth. Seek them out, as they will help along your journey.
name: The Lost Rune

title: Relics of the Light
objective: Recover the libram and follow its guidance to learn a new ability, then return to Brother Sammuel in Northshire.
description:
Relics of the Light can be found across Azeroth. These relics - in particular, the Librams that have guided our order since its founding - can help you strengthen your connection to the Light.

One such libram was held in the Abbey's archives, but it has been stolen by the Defias bandits to the east. Recover the libram, then study it and follow its guidance to learn a new combat technique. Return to me when you have done this.
_progress: What has the libram revealed to you, <name>?
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune you have learned to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

Seek out more of these relics along your travels.
name: Relics of the Light

title: Thrice Stolen
objective: Recover the lost rune from the Defias camps and use it to learn a new ability, then return to Jorik Kerridan in Northshire.
description:
I'm ashamed to admit it, <name>, but those Defias jerks got the drop on me. They stole a magical rune I... uh, 'borrowed' from the Abbey's archives. I figured it would give me some kinda advantage in a fix, but I couldn't crack how to make it work.

Make your way east and see if you can snatch it back from their stash, would ya? And try to use the rune yourself, when you find it. You seem like a bookish sort. No offense.
_complete:
A fine bit of larceny there, <name>. Consider that rune a present from yours truly.

If Brother Paxton asks, we never had this conversation, yeah?
name: Thrice Stolen

title: Meditation on the Light
objective: Slay kobolds in Echo Ridge Mine to receive a memory. Kneel within Northshire Abbey to meditate on the light, then use the memory to learn a new ability. Afterwards, return to Priestess Anetta.
description:
The Light has shown me your future, fighting the kobolds in Echo Ridge Mine. Within the mine, the Light will grant you a memory of the past. Once this is revealed to you, return to the Abbey and kneel within these halls to meditate on the Light's mysteries.

Once you have focused your thoughts, you will be able to make sense of this memory and learn a new technique. Return to me when you have done this.
_progress: What has the Light revealed to you?
_complete:
As the Light reveals more visions to you, you can always meditate at sacred sites to clear your thoughts and contemplate these mysteries.

I have also foreseen that your path will lead you to commune with our elven allies in Kalimdor. Learning more about their curious moon-worship rituals may help us someday lead them to the Light as well.
name: Meditation on the Light

title: Spell Research
objective: Recover research notes from the Defias bandits and use them to learn a new spell, then return to Khelden Bremen in Northshire.
description:
I will teach you what I can, <name>, but your own research will lead to astonishing power. Studying notes left by Azeroth's greatest archmages is an excellent place to start. The Abbey's archives used to contain a myriad of arcane research notes, but they were stolen by Defias agents.

Recover spell notes from the bandits to the east and use this primer to decipher them. Return to me once your research is successful.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Take these Comprehension Charms. They will help you decipher any more arcane writings you find.

Continue to seek out spell notes across Azeroth and use them to further your research. If you need more charms, pay a visit to a reagent vendor.
name: Spell Research

title: Stolen Power
objective: Recover the rune from the Defias camps to the east and use it to learn a new ability, then return to Drusilla La Salle in Northshire.
description:
I've been experimenting with a new type of magic - a rune which can channel fel energies to fuel powerful spells. I would share this power with you, but my notes were stolen last night. I suspect the bandits calling themselves the 'Defias' are to blame.

Go to the east, and see if you can find my rune stashed among their possessions. Learn its magic, and report back to me. I would like to see my experiment put to use.
_complete:
You seem to have taken well to this new magic, <name>. Find more runes like this and engrave them to your equipment to wield new abilities against those who would oppose you.

Someday, perhaps your power will even eclipse my own.
name: Stolen Power

title: Wisdom of the Loa
objective: Kneel at the Loa Altar in Sen'jin Village. Commune with the Loa spirit, then use the memory to learn a new ability. Afterwards, return to Ken'jai  in the Valley of Trails.
description:
Joining the Horde has given our people a safe home, <name>, but we must remember that it is the Loa who are always watching over us.

Now, clear your mind, and I will share an ancient memory with you. Go to the Loa Altar in Sen'jin Village, and kneel before it to commune with the great Loa spirit. Once you have received the Loa's wisdom, you will come to understand the memory I have given you. Through this understanding, you will discover a new power.

Return to me once you have done this.
_progress: What have the Loa taught you, <name>?
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

The Loa will grant you many more memories along your journey. You can pray at Loa Altars across Azeroth to clear your thoughts and interpret them, as you have just done.

Understanding more complex visions may require the help of fellow priests within the Horde. Do not be afraid to learn from their faith, <name>. The wisdom of the Loa can be found in all things.
name: Wisdom of the Loa

title: Spell Research
objective: Find the stolen spell notes inside the Burning Blade Coven, then use them to learn a new ability. Afterwards, return to Mai'ah in the Valley of Trails.
description:
As a mage, researching the arcane will lead you to astonishing power. Studying notes left by Azeroth's greatest mages is an excellent place to start. I had recently discovered some myself, but they were stolen by those pesky Burning Blade Familiars.

Recover the spell notes from the coven to the north and use this primer to decipher them. Return when your research is successful.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Take these Comprehension Charms. They will help you decipher any more arcane writings you find.

Continue to seek out spell notes across Azeroth and use them to further your research. If you need more charms, pay a visit to a reagent vendor.
name: Spell Research

title: Relics of the Tauren
objective: Recover the stolen relic from Brambleblade Ravine. Follow the relic's guidance to learn a new ability, then report back to Gart Mistrunner in Camp Narache.
description:
The Tauren are an ancient people, <name>, and our lost relics can be found across Azeroth. Through them, the spirits can teach you ways to strengthen your connection to the Dream.

The bristleback quilboar have stolen one such relic from us. They have likely stashed it away within Brambleblade Ravine.  Recover the relic, and follow its guidance to learn a new combat technique. Return to me when you have done this.
_progress: What has the relic taught you. <name>?
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune you have learned to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

Seek out more of our lost relics along your travels.
name: Relics of the Tauren

title: A Hunter's Strength

description:
Hunters are central to the Tauren way of life, <name>. Our people look to us as both guardians and providers. Many times on your journey, you will alone in hostile territory, surviving only by your wits.

Not long ago, a fledgling hunter was experimenting with mystical runes to improve his combat prowess. He went out to test his new abilities on the Bristleback Battleboars to the east, but never returned.

Find his rune, and use it to learn a new combat technique. Return to me once you have done so.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

_complete:
As the Light reveals more visions to you, you can always meditate at sacred sites to clear your thoughts and contemplate these mysteries.

I have also foreseen that your path will lead you to commune with our elven allies in Kalimdor. Learning more about their curious moon-worship rituals may help us someday lead them to the Light as well.
name: Meditation on the Light

title: Stolen Power
objective: Recover the rune from the group of Troggs, southwest of Anvilmar, and use it to learn a new ability. Then, return to Alamar Grimm in Anvilmar.
description:
I've been experimenting with a new type of magic - a rune which can channel fel energy to fuel powerful spells. I would share this power with you, but it was stolen by one of those pesky troggs.

There is a camp of those Rockjaw vermin to the southwest. See if you can find my rune stashed among their possessions, likely in a chest of some kind. Once you find it, learn its magic and report back to me. I would like to see my experiment put to use.
_complete:
You seem to have taken well to this new magic, <name>. Find more runes like this and engrave them to your equipment. Wield this power against those who would oppose you.

Someday, perhaps your power will even eclipse my own.
name: Stolen Power

title: Spell Research
objective: Find the stolen spell notes at the trogg camp to the southwest of Anvilmar, then use them to learn a new ability. Afterwards, return to Marryk Nurribit in Anvilmar.
description:
As a mage, researching the arcane will lead you to astonishing power. Studying notes left by Azeroth's greatest mages is an excellent place to start. I had recently discovered some myself, but they were stolen by those pesky troggs to the southwest.

Recover the spell notes from the troggs' camp and use this primer to make sense of them. Return when your research is successful.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Take these Comprehension Charms. They will help you decipher any more arcane writings you find.

Continue to seek out spell notes across Azeroth and use them to further your research. If you need more charms, pay a visit to a reagent vendor.
name: Spell Research

title: The Lost Rune
objective: Find the rune hidden in Night Web's Hollow and use it to learn a new technique, then report back to Dannal Stern in Deathknell.
description:
The Dark Lady's warriors have much to teach you, but you must also seek out new techniques on your own.

Another warrior recently ventured north into Night Web's Hollow. He was experimenting with engraving mystical runes onto his equipment to improve his combat prowess.

I suspect he was overwhelmed by the spiders infesting the mine. Find the rune among their webs and learn this technique yourself.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

There are many such runes throughout Azeroth. Seek them out, as they will help along your journey.
name: The Lost Rune

title: The Scarlet Rune
objective: Pickpocket or kill Scarlet Converts to find a rune, then use it to learn a new ability. Afterwards, return to David Trias in Deathknell.
description:
Who were you in life, <name>? A spy? A thief? A cook who was especially handy with a knife? Whatever your past, it's time to embrace new tactics. The rogues of the Forsaken seize every advantage offered to them.

The Scarlet Converts to the east fight like they've never seen combat, but the Crusade has issued them mystical runes to enhance their abilities. Steal one of these runes and learn its magic, then return to me.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Applying the rune to your equipment will grant you powerful new abilities.

There are many such runes throughout Azeroth. Seek them out, as they will help along your journey.
name: The Scarlet Rune

title: Meditation on Undeath
objective: Kneel in the graveyard to meditate on undeath, then use the rune to learn a new ability. Afterwards, return to Dark Cleric Duesten in the Deathknell chapel.
description: I will summon to your mind a memory of the living - it may even be your own memory. Go to the graveyard beside this chapel and find where the chill of death is strongest, then kneel and focus your thoughts. Through focus on the mysteries of undeath you will find clarity in this memory and learn a new technique. Return to me when you have done this.
_progress: If you have difficulty focusing on death, you could try dying again. It's unlikely to be permanent the second time either.
_complete:
The living cling to the Light for one reason - they fear the oblivion of death. As Forsaken, that fear has no further hold over you. Though the Light now rejects even those among us who were once its most fervent devotees, we command dark powers that lie beyond death's shadow.

As you grow stronger I recommend spending some time with the trolls of the Horde. Though their culture is primitive, the 'loa' they revere have some connection to undeath. They may provide insight into our nature.
name: Meditation on Undeath

title: Spell Research
objective: Kill Scarlet Initiates to find spell notes and use them to learn a new ability, then return to Isabella in Deathknell.
description:
The arcanists of the Royal Apothecary Society commit their unlife to spell research in service to the Forsaken. Adventure may be your calling, but you can serve the Dark Lady by securing and researching spell notes you find in your travels.

Kill the Scarlet Crusade initiates camped near Deathknell, and seize their spell notes. Use this primer to decipher the notes and learn a new spell, then return to me.
_complete:
Well done, <name>. Take these Comprehension Charms. They will help you decipher any more arcane writings you find.

Continue to seek out spell notes across Azeroth and use them to further your research. If you need more charms, pay a visit to a reagent vendor.
name: Spell Research

title: The Lost Rune
objective: Recover the rune from Night Web's Hollow and use it to learn a new ability, then return to Maximillion in Deathknell.
description:
I've been experimenting with a new type of magic - a rune which can channel fel energies to fuel powerful spells. I sent an apprentice to test the rune against the spiders in the mine to the north, but he has not returned. I suspect we will not see him again.

Perhaps you will prove more resilient. Go to the mine and recover the rune from the spiders' webs. Learn its magic, and report back to me.
_complete:
You seem to have taken well to this new magic, <name>. Find more runes like this and engrave them to your equipment to wield new abilities against those who would oppose you.

Someday, perhaps your power will even eclipse my own.
name: The Lost Rune

title: Sharing the Faith
objective: Meditate on the Light, then pray with the kneeling elf to share your meditations.
description:
The Light calls us to justice and protection, but also compassion. Our allies are strangers in our lands and we have a duty to teach them our ways.
This Night Elf seeks the Light, but is struggling in his meditation. Would you assist him?
_complete: The Light works its blessings through you, <name>. Honor it by continuing to share your wisdom with supplicants you meet in your travels.
name: Sharing the Faith

title: Sharing the Faith
objective: Meditate on Elune, then pray with the kneeling human to share your meditations.
description: This human grasps for Elune's light, but his sight is clouded. Would you assist him?
_complete: The Light works its blessings through you, <name>. Honor it by continuing to share your wisdom with supplicants you meet in your travels.
name: Sharing the Faith

title: Sharing the Faith
objective: Meditate on the Loa, then pray with the kneeling Forsaken to share your meditations.
description: This poor Forsaken priest can't seem to find a loa who will bargain with him. Maybe you could give him a blessing instead?
_complete: The undead aren't too popular with the loa, but it's good of you to help this one out. Try to show some pity for them if you meet any more who need help, yeah?
name: Sharing the Faith

title: Sharing the Faith
objective: Meditate on undeath, then pray with the kneeling troll to share your meditations.
description: This Troll is reflecting on death, but lacks a certain... familiarity with the topic. Please help to clarify his understanding.
_complete: In my experience, our people are at best a curiosity to the rest of the Horde. Still, sharing our knowledge is a simple way to gain their trust. Keep that in mind along your travels.
name: Sharing the Faith
